---
import ContentLayout from '../../layouts/ContentLayout.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<ContentLayout title="Questions" section="questions" description="Curated questions for walking, talking, and reflecting on pilgrimage.">
  <p>
    We've curated 65 questions from the original 950 at
    <a href="https://savewisdom.org">savewisdom.org</a>, organized by
    how and when you'll use them.
  </p>

  <h2>How to Use</h2>

  <p>
    Each question is tagged with a <strong>stage</strong> — opening, middle, or
    closing — to help you choose based on where you are in your pilgrimage or
    conversation. Opening questions are lighter and build connection. Middle
    questions go deeper. Closing questions invite synthesis and reflection.
  </p>

  <p>
    Don't rush through them. One good question per walk or one per evening
    discussion is more than enough. Let the question breathe.
  </p>

  <h2>By Context</h2>

  <div class="grid gap-4 not-prose mt-6">
    <a href={`${base}questions/walking/`} class="block p-6 rounded-xl bg-white/50 border border-secondary/15 hover:border-accent/30 transition-colors">
      <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-text mb-2">Walking Questions</h3>
      <p class="text-text/60 text-base">~25 lighter prompts for side-by-side conversations while in motion.</p>
    </a>

    <a href={`${base}questions/evening/`} class="block p-6 rounded-xl bg-white/50 border border-secondary/15 hover:border-accent/30 transition-colors">
      <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-text mb-2">Evening Discussion</h3>
      <p class="text-text/60 text-base">~15 deep questions for Jeffersonian-style group conversations. One per evening.</p>
    </a>

    <a href={`${base}questions/solo/`} class="block p-6 rounded-xl bg-white/50 border border-secondary/15 hover:border-accent/30 transition-colors">
      <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-text mb-2">Solo Reflection</h3>
      <p class="text-text/60 text-base">~15 introspective prompts for journaling or voice recording during rest stops.</p>
    </a>

    <a href={`${base}questions/morning/`} class="block p-6 rounded-xl bg-white/50 border border-secondary/15 hover:border-accent/30 transition-colors">
      <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-text mb-2">Morning Seeds</h3>
      <p class="text-text/60 text-base">~10 one-sentence prompts to carry into the day from morning meditation.</p>
    </a>
  </div>

  <h2>Credit</h2>

  <p>
    All questions are sourced from the 950 questions at
    <a href="https://savewisdom.org">savewisdom.org</a>. We've selected the ones
    most relevant to pilgrimage — open-ended, cross-cultural, and designed to
    invite depth rather than quick answers.
  </p>
</ContentLayout>
